\\n    private static String read(Reader reader) throws IOException {\\n        StringWriter writer = new StringWriter();\\n        char[] buffer = new char[256];\\n        int count;\\n        try (reader) {\\n            while ((count = reader.read(buffer)) != -1) {\\n                writer.write(buffer, 0, count);\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return writer.toString();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777655293513}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-08-27-828177Z.log:2028:[thinking] I'm considering if coordinate metadata is untracked, suggesting that our files might be untracked simply due to the parent path being partially tracked but containing new files. I notice that `git diff --stat` may not show untracked files, which could be a crucial point. I just need to refine my thoughts and present a clear conclusion about the tracking status of these files without getting lost in too many details.\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-08-27-828177Z.log:2032:[assistant] Implemented dedicated `Resolver` dynamic-access coverage tests.\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser:dtd-parser:1.5.1/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-01T17-08-27-828177Z.log:2046:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying Git tracking**\\n\\nI'm considering if coordinate metadata is untracked, suggesting that our files might be untracked simply due to the parent path being partially tracked but containing new files. I notice that `git diff --stat` may not show untracked files, which could be a crucial point. I just need to refine my thoughts and present a clear conclusion about the tracking status of these files without getting lost in too many details.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\