the current class, MessageCatalog. Since MessageCatalog is boot-loaded, it will use the bootstrap loader instead of the app loader. Uh oh! So when it tries to load `Messages_es`, it’s attempting to do so with the bootstrap context. This feels a bit tricky, as I need to ensure the right loader is being utilized in this scenario.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_lTWH0ousJs0wCJMiwvu1PnVT|fc_053f396fbad82c020169f4dc4eb2cc81939397a265cc3c4098\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/src/bootstrapProbe/java/com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/resources/Messages_es.java\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_sun_xml_dtd_parser.dtd_parser.resources;\\n\\nimport java.util.ListResourceBundle;\\n\\npublic class Messages_es extends ListResourceBundle {\\n    @Override\\n    protected Object[][] getContents() {\\n        return new Object[][] {\\n                {\\\"plain\\\", \\\"Spanish class-backed message\\\"}\\n        };\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_yiuGiSyllmV6X5XGrHvMwM15|fc_053f396fbad82c020169f4dc4eb2dc81938a83ab4e29bf7d8d\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"rm -rf tests/src/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser/1.5.1/src/test/java/com_sun_xml_dtd_parser/dtd_parser/resources\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1467, \"output\": 1105, \"cacheRead\": 46080, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 48652, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777654848607, \"responseId\": \"resp_053f396fbad82c020169f4dc4130b48193899d978e473aea3c\"}}\n4396:[tool-exec] end id=call_lTWH0ou